pageContext.claim: “[DeSantis] went up 60 points after I endorsed him. Ron won. And he's been a great governor of Florida. You know, I've always heard that an endorsement is nice to have but it doesn't mean anything. I'm driving people up 30%, 40%, 50%, 60%.”
pageContext.analysis: Florida Gov. Ron DeSantis (R) won by less than 35,000 votes, despite Trump’s endorsement.
